      "body" : "@luke-jr Signing a message with a change address proves that the signer controls the change address that sent a transaction.  Why would you argue for removing useful functionality?\r\n\r\nWhat does it even mean to say \"Signed messages only work for receiving, not for sending\"?  Signing a message with an address is unrelated to sending or receiving a transaction.",
