   {
      "body" : "@dooglus Signing proves you *receive* at the address. Just because you receive at a given address, does not mean you sent the coins in a later transaction consuming the outputs (and indeed, the contrary is often true). Addresses are only used for receiving, not for sending.\r\n\r\nIf people need the ability to prove they sent a transaction, some new standard (whereby they sign with a transaction instead of an address) is needed.",
